g>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3615507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qsr1665702851284.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsr1665702851284.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsr1665702851284.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qsr1665702851284\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      ImgSidebar\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Name of the image file or glyph to use as the background of the menu sidebar.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__topic_d110066e1_d110067e1_d110068e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110069e1_d110070e1_d110071e1\">This property can only be set in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[application]\nmenu=umenu(imgsidebar=@ImageName | ^<var class=\"keyword varname\">GlyphName</var>)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__section_fgy_ngl_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1007020e66\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110075e1_d110076e1_d110077e1\">By default, menus in Windows have a sidebar to the\n        left of the menu items (or to the right if the application is configured for a right-to-left\n        character set). This space is reserved to display images associated with the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110078e1_d110079e1_d110080e1\">You can use the ImgSidebar to specify a background\n        image for menu sidebar. If you specify a small image, it is automatically stretched to fit\n        the width of the menu.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110081e1_d110082e1_d110083e1\">If ImgSidebar is defined, the BackColorSidebar\n        property is ignored.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__section_vqy_4gl_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1007020e81\">Example: Setting ImgSidebar</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110087e1_d110088e1_d110089e1\">The following properties, set in the\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file, specify images to be used as the background for the\n        menu sidebar and the selected menu item.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__pre_ehm_1hl_cxb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[application]\nmenu=umenu(imgsidebar=@blue.png;imgSelect=yellow.png)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__section_c55_qgl_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1007020e96\">Applies To</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsr1665702851284__p_d110093e1_d110094e1_d110095e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vfw1705577424699.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vfw1705577424699.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to define menu bar, drop-down menu, and pop-up menu objects for use in Windows applications.\">Menu Objects</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oam1665702851070.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>BackColorSidebar</a><p>Color to use as the background of the sidebar in a menu. Valid value is a web or system color name, or a hexadecimal number (prefixed by a hash mark). If not specified, the Windows system default is used.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ImgSidebar Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 ImgSidebar Name of the image file or glyph to use as the background of the menu sidebar. This property can only be set in the .ini file. [application] menu=umenu(imgsidebar=@ImageName | ^ GlyphName ) Copy Description By default, menus in Windows have a sidebar to the left of the menu items (or to the right if the application is configured for a right-to-left character set). This space is reserved to display images associated with the menu item. You can use the ImgSidebar to specify a background image for menu sidebar. If you specify a small image, it is automatically stretched to fit the width of the menu. If ImgSidebar is defined, the BackColorSidebar property is ignored. Example: Setting ImgSidebar The following properties, set in the usys.ini file, specify images to be used as the background for the menu sidebar and the selected menu item. [application] menu=umenu(imgsidebar=@blue.png;imgSelect=yellow.png) Copy Applies To Menu Objects Related Links BackColorSidebar Color to use as the background of the sidebar in a menu. Valid value is a web or system color name, or a hexadecimal number (prefixed by a hash mark). If not specified, the Windows system default is used. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}